          <!-- slide 21 -->
          <article id="slide-yGj4Oz">

            <div class="slide layout-middle contains-1 contains-heading has-heading all- has-bg-image">
              <div class="slide-inner-wrap">
                <div class="slide-inner">
                  <div class="slide-content">
                      <div class="e e-1 e-heading">
                        <h1 class="heading">
  
</h1>

                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>


            <aside class="narrative">
                <p>
	Manufacturing halfway around the world is progressively easier for companies of all sizes. Highway1 and HAXLR8R take prototype-stage companies to China to help them learn the factory ecosystem. Alibaba is essentially the front-end to the supplier marketplaces such as HQB in Shenzhen. Even Fortune 500s rely on the full-stack manufacturing, fulfillment, and supply chain management solutions offered by partners such as PCH, Flextronics, and Foxconn.
</p>
            </aside>
          </article>
          <!-- slide 22 -->
          <article id="slide-g3bDEy">

            <div class="slide layout-middle contains-1 contains-heading has-heading all- has-bg-image">
              <div class="slide-inner-wrap">
                <div class="slide-inner">
                  <div class="slide-content">
                      <div class="e e-1 e-heading">
                        <h1 class="heading">
  
</h1>

                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>


            <aside class="narrative">
                <p>
	     It’s no longer obvious where to manufacture.
</p>
<p>
	    In Silicon Valley Bank’s Startup Outlook 2013 survey, 58% of hardware startups say that they will do at least some manufacturing within the United States.
</p>
<p>
	     In a BCG survey, somewhere between 37-54% of companies with annual sales exceeding $1 billion said they are planning to or actively considering reshoring.
</p>
<p>
	 [<a href="http://www.svb.com/startup-outlook-report/" rel="nofollow">source</a>]<br>
	[<a href="http://www.bcg.com/media/pressreleasedetails.aspx?id=tcm:12-144944" rel="nofollow">source</a>]
</p>
